benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache/tenants - Invalidates Caches per tenant level

covered: Valid Deletion: Successful DELETE invalidates tenant cache (204) with empty body
Empty Response: DELETE responses include empty body on success (204)
Non-Existent Resource: Returns 404 when tenant context does not exist
Concurrency: Handles multiple concurrent DELETE requests for the same tenant (no data corruption; idempotent)
Authorization: Tests cover missing and invalid credentials (401) scenarios
Malformed Request: 400 on malformed/unsupported parameters or payload
Security: Injection-like header payload handled (400 or 403)
System Error Handling: 500 internal server error scenario covered
Integration: Dependent services observe cache invalidation
State Variation: Partially populated tenant cache results in 204 with invalidation
Regression: Previously fixed error does not recur (204)
Performance under load: Concurrency under load with acceptable response times
Edge case: Idempotent operation when cache already empty (204)
gaps: Soft Deletes: No explicit test verifying physical vs soft delete behavior
Rate Limiting: No explicit test for rate limiting/throttling
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching layer behavior
Pagination: Not applicable for cache deletion but not tested (likely not needed)
recommendations: Add tests for soft-delete semantics to clarify deletion behavior
Add rate-limiting tests to validate throttling and error handling under load
Add tests for caching headers and caching behavior to ensure proper cache-control semantics
Consider a dedicated test for idempotency across repeated DELETE calls in various scenarios (different tenants)
